{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"115c2d10-44e0-11ed-850d-1de45ed8df23","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"509b7ba7-b1e9-4e10-a4b3-200c276f3528","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The Takeover Process","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"08bbe6e3-ee71-4408-8c02-5183da5bdf32"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":4},"ref":"7ee47d42-71c3-421b-ac67-cf2fa653ca38","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"7572c263-c242-483f-ab3e-0904d1a88d55","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"55597ac5-a2e9-4d95-ad13-dfb2e71d9bb9","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Loki, Inc., and Thor, Inc., have entered into a stock-swap merger agreement whereby Loki will pay a 40% premium over Thor’s premerger price. If Thor’s premerger price per share was $40 and Loki’s was $50, what exchange ratio will Loki need to offer?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"321f69b5-984f-4d43-9409-9763ec412984","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"dd94a2c8-291e-4628-8ed9-b5f65fa02f44","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The NFF Corporation has announced plans to acquire LE Corporation. NFF is trading at $35 per share and LE is trading at $25 per share, implying a premerger value of LE of $4 billion. If the projected synergies are $1 billion, what is the maximum exchange ratio NFF could offer in a stock swap and still generate a positive NPV?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d71915cb-0a0f-4b0f-a00a-10b59626b069","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"6f6ab284-b12d-49a9-8221-999d08053634","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Let’s reconsider Problem 1 (b). The actual premium that your company will pay for TargetCo when it completes the transaction will not be 20%, because on the announcement the target price will go up and your price will go down to reflect the fact that you are willing to pay a premium for TargetCo without any synergies. Assume that the takeover will occur with certainty and all market participants know this on the announcement of the takeover (ignore time value of money).","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"8f313ea8-f8a0-454e-b894-9b7a5e0936f7","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"6685c9d4-2f09-4f63-af60-652dd73b20ca","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"f3fa01a2-4abc-4241-af64-a133308e5a43","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the price per share of the combined corporation immediately after the merger is completed?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"0c0005f6-d4f3-4ebf-8ec4-f41478af1355","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"064a8b21-7dd7-47ec-843e-ca5d03230d7b","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the price of your company immediately after the announcement?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d09f014e-1b59-446d-b287-f97f307ade24","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"b19c8bde-d77a-43bf-b8b5-905a916eb506","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the price of TargetCo immediately after the announcement?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"657921a1-0996-4403-8237-7d729eeca095","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"1d0ab006-8482-466c-b377-504717725dd3","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the actual premium your company will pay?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"5a0650bd-c32b-4156-b302-58c51a9ee879","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ffef0254-175e-40f8-a054-c1c554d7078f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"ABC has 1 million shares outstanding, each of which has a price of $20. It has made a takeover offer of XYZ Corporation, which has 1 million shares outstanding and a price per share of $2.50. Assume that the takeover will occur with certainty and all market participants know this. Furthermore, there are no synergies to merging the two firms.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"d70d0abb-3c23-4c24-b97a-3fe9a85ca71b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"777413ce-70b8-4c64-abcd-a60dcb75268e","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a40fafb9-328c-4801-8a3f-a72b51fe857c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume ABC made a cash offer to purchase XYZ for $3 million. What happens to the price of ABC and XYZ on the announcement? What premium over the current market price does this offer represent?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"bacb720c-f651-4c10-97c5-1288a7846e7b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"c99efec4-d3ca-4928-8895-ecac124a1db3","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume ABC makes a stock offer with an exchange ratio of 0.15. What happens to the price of ABC and XYZ this time? What premium over the current market price does this offer represent?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"72df0986-af0a-4814-a67d-133260027cf4","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"351328d3-5278-4d37-9036-615efe3111f2","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"At current market prices, both offers are to purchase XYZ for $3 million. Does that mean that your answers to (a) and (b) must be identical? Explain.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"acea428d-65b5-42e1-a9b6-458eafbcec43"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"The Takeover Process"},"assets":[],"scenarios":[],"pluginPayload":{"pluginRepositoryPath":"https://plugin-repository-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8/0.15.209/ac43ee4c0eda05e9718fa83a5aed4cff.zip","summary":{"pluginId":"9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8","